{# templates/roadmaps/real-state/legal-liability.html.twig #}
{% extends 'base-roadmaps.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_link_tags('real_state_css') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('real_state_js') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="container">
        <!-- Article Hero -->
        <div class="article-hero animate" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2f2a24 0%, #5e4b3f 100%);">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-icon" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">
                    <i class="fas fa-gavel"></i>
                </div>
                <h1>Legal & Liability Risks <span>Insurance and LLCs</span></h1>
                <p class="hero-description">
                    A single lawsuit could wipe out years of real estate profits. Learn how to protect your personal assets with proper insurance and legal structures like LLCs.
                </p>
                <div class="phase-tag" style="background-color: rgba(225,112,85,0.2); color: #f7b9a9;">
                    <i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Phase 2: Risk Management · 9 min read
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <section class="animate">
            <h2 class="section-title">🛡️ Don't Let a Lawsuit Take Everything</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                As a landlord, you face unique legal risks: tenant injuries, discrimination claims, property damage, and more.
                <strong>Without proper protection, your personal savings, home, and future investments are at risk.</strong>
                This guide covers the two main shields: insurance and the Limited Liability Company (LLC).
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Key Protection Layers (using rule-grid) -->
        <div class="rule-grid animate">
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Landlord Insurance</h4>
                <p>Specialized coverage for rental properties: dwelling, liability, loss of rent, and medical payments. Required by most lenders and essential for all landlords.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-umbrella"></i> Umbrella Insurance</h4>
                <p>Extra liability coverage above your auto and landlord policies. Typically $1–5 million for a few hundred dollars a year. Critical for high‑net‑worth individuals.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-building"></i> LLC (Limited Liability Company)</h4>
                <p>A legal entity that separates business assets from personal assets. If you're sued, only the assets inside the LLC are at risk – your personal wealth stays protected.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Proper Documentation</h4>
                <p>Well‑written leases, inspection reports, and maintenance records can prevent disputes and strengthen your legal position.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Deeper Dive Card -->
        <div class="card animate">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-scale-balanced"></i> LLC vs. Insurance: Do You Need Both?</h3>
            <p><strong>Insurance is your first line of defense.</strong> It covers claims and legal costs up to policy limits. But it won't protect you if the claim exceeds your coverage.</p>
            <p><strong>An LLC provides a corporate veil.</strong> If you're properly structured and operated, a lawsuit against the LLC can't touch your personal assets. However, you must keep business and personal finances strictly separate.</p>
            <p style="background: var(--light-gray); padding: 15px; border-radius: 12px;">
                <strong>Most experts recommend:</strong> Landlord insurance + umbrella policy + LLC for each property (or a series LLC). The combination gives maximum protection.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Interactive Tool: Asset Protection Simulator (disabled for non-logged-in) -->
        <div class="card animate" id="liability-simulator">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-pie"></i> Interactive: Asset Protection Simulator</h3>
            <p>See how much of your wealth is at risk in a lawsuit scenario with different protection strategies.</p>

            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Your Total Personal Assets ($) <span id="personalAssetsVal">500000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="personalAssets" min="50000" max="5000000" value="500000" step="10000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Property Value ($) <span id="propertyValLegal">300000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="propertyValue" min="50000" max="2000000" value="300000" step="10000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Lawsuit Claim Amount ($) <span id="claimVal">500000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="claimAmount" min="10000" max="2000000" value="500000" step="10000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Insurance Coverage ($) <span id="insuranceValLegal">300000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="insuranceCoverage" min="100000" max="2000000" value="300000" step="50000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Umbrella Policy ($) <span id="umbrellaVal">1000000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="umbrellaCoverage" min="0" max="5000000" value="1000000" step="100000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>LLC in place?</label>
                    <select id="hasLLC" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                        <option value="no">No</option>
                        <option value="yes">Yes</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <button id="simulateLiability" class="btn-outline">Simulate Protection</button>
            </div>

            <div id="liabilityResult" style="margin-top: 25px; padding: 20px; background: var(--light-color); border-radius: 12px;">
                <p>Adjust the values and click the button.</p>
            </div>

            <p class="pro-tip" style="margin-top: 15px;">
                <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> This simulator assumes a lawsuit where you are found liable. Actual legal outcomes vary. Consult an attorney for personalized advice.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Quick Comparison Table -->
        <div class="card animate">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-table"></i> Insurance vs. LLC: Quick Comparison</h3>
            <table style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse;">
                <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--real-estate-color);">
                    <th style="text-align: left; padding: 8px;">Feature</th>
                    <th style="text-align: left; padding: 8px;">Landlord Insurance</th>
                    <th style="text-align: left; padding: 8px;">Umbrella Policy</th>
                    <th style="text-align: left; padding: 8px;">LLC</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Protects personal assets</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Only up to policy limit</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Yes, up to limit</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Yes, if properly maintained</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Cost</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Moderate</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Low ($150–$500/year for $1M)</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">One‑time filing + annual fees</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Complexity</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Simple</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Simple</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Requires separate bank accounts, tax returns</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Coverage for tenant claims</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Yes</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Yes</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">No (but limits exposure)</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>

        <!-- Quiz Section -->
        {% if app.user and quiz is defined and quiz %}
            {# Logged in user – quiz already taken #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">🧠 You've already taken this quiz</h3>
                <p style="color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 1.2rem;">
                    Your score: <strong>{{ quiz.quizzScore }}%</strong>
                </p>
                <p style="color: #cbd5e0;">
                    You can retake the quiz to improve your score. Click the button below to reset it.
                </p>
                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'legal-liability', retake: 1 }) }}"
                       class="btn"
                       style="background-color: #e17055; color: white; text-decoration: none;">
                        Retake Quiz
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        {% else %}
            {# Show quiz (interactivity blocked by JS if not logged in) #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" data-page-id="{{ page.id }}" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">📝 Test Your Knowledge: Legal & Liability</h3>

                <div class="quiz-question">1. What is the primary purpose of a landlord insurance policy?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="1">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">To cover the tenant's belongings</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">To protect the property and provide liability coverage</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">To pay for routine maintenance</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">To guarantee rental income</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">2. An umbrella insurance policy provides:</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="2">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Health insurance for landlords</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Extra liability coverage above other policies</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Protection against natural disasters</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Coverage for tenant discrimination claims</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">3. What does an LLC (Limited Liability Company) protect?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="3">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Your personal assets from business lawsuits</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">The property itself from damage</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">You from tenant disputes</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Your credit score</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">4. Which of the following is a common mistake that can "pierce the corporate veil" of an LLC?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="4">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Having insurance</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Mixing personal and business funds</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Filing annual reports</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Having a written lease</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">5. If you have a $500,000 landlord policy and a $1M umbrella, what is your total liability coverage in a lawsuit?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="5">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">$500,000</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">$1,000,000</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">$1,500,000 (usually umbrella sits on top)</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">$500,000 + legal fees</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <button id="quiz-submit" class="btn" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">Get score & submit</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-result"></div>
            </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- Next Steps in Phase 2 -->
        <section style="margin: 60px 0;">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">📘 Complete Phase 2: Risk Management</h2>
            <div class="next-steps">
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'real-estate-market-risk' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
                    <h3>Market Risk & Cycles</h3>
                    <p>Understand booms and busts.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'hidden-costs' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-wrench"></i>
                    <h3>Hidden Costs</h3>
                    <p>Taxes, insurance, maintenance.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'vacancy-risk' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-door-open"></i>
                    <h3>Vacancy Risk</h3>
                    <p>Minimize empty units.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
